<h1>@KJ{{going}}@HI{{tte}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<strong>@Nplace{{}} @HI{{he}} @KJ{{going}}@HI{{tte}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}</strong>

<h2> Definition </h2>

This sentence pattern is used when the speaker means to say "to go somewhere  and come back"
without specifying what might be done at the remote destination.

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{mail^convenience^bureau}}he <strong>@KJ{{going}}tte @KJ{{come}}masu</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I'm going to the post office (and coming back).
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

